        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, chop your <strong>basil</strong> finely, including the stalks</p><p>Grind the <strong>chopped basil</strong> with a small pinch of <strong>salt</strong> in a <strong>pestle & mortar</strong> to form a paste</p><p>Add your <strong>red wine vinegar</strong> with a pinch of <strong>sugar</strong> and 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3 tbsp] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp] </span><strong>olive oil</strong> and mix well – this is your <strong>basil oil</strong></p><p>Tip: If you don't have a pestle & mortar, chop the basil leaves very finely and mix with salt, olive oil and vinegar</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
